We're pinned to the
one side of that--

00:40:40.105 --> 00:40:40.906 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Absolutely.

00:40:40.906 --> 00:40:42.007 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: -- polarity and only

00:40:42.007 --> 00:40:45.544 align:middle line:84%
that hyper masculine
mode gets reinforcement.

00:40:45.544 --> 00:40:47.779 align:middle line:90%
And we're all dealing--

00:40:47.779 --> 00:40:50.048 align:middle line:84%
you might say the
symptoms of the disease

00:40:50.048 --> 00:40:54.586 align:middle line:84%
of that hyper masculine fixation
to simply allow ourselves to be

00:40:54.586 --> 00:40:58.356 align:middle line:84%
with ourselves, to be
with our own experience,

00:40:58.356 --> 00:41:02.527 align:middle line:84%
to be with our loved ones,
to take in his breath,

00:41:02.527 --> 00:41:07.632 align:middle line:84%
to take in the miracle of this
moment, to take in the beauty

00:41:07.632 --> 00:41:12.504 align:middle line:84%
of your smile, to
actually feel the heart

00:41:12.504 --> 00:41:14.206 align:middle line:90%
that is always present.

00:41:14.206 --> 00:41:15.974 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:41:15.974 --> 00:41:19.744 align:middle line:84%
OK. Now, let's go into the
unhealthy aspect of activism

00:41:19.744 --> 00:41:23.882 align:middle line:84%
and you call it anxiety
produced activism.

00:41:23.882 --> 00:41:25.217 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:41:25.217 --> 00:41:27.152 align:middle line:84%
It's where we're not-- where
you were just a moment ago.

00:41:27.152 --> 00:41:29.321 align:middle line:84%
We're not breathing in
and we're not breathing

00:41:29.321 --> 00:41:33.258 align:middle line:84%
out in this wonderful flow
between the two aspects mind.

00:41:33.258 --> 00:41:35.860 align:middle line:84%
Instead, we seem to have gotten
stocked into something else.

00:41:35.860 --> 00:41:39.264 align:middle line:84%
So, what is anxiety
produced activism?

00:41:39.264 --> 00:41:42.334 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: Most of the activism that
you all are aware of that we see

00:41:42.334 --> 00:41:44.703 align:middle line:84%
on the TV everyday,
most of the marches,

00:41:44.703 --> 00:41:48.340 align:middle line:84%
most of the impassioning
speeches, most of the protests,

00:41:48.340 --> 00:41:53.712 align:middle line:84%
most of the political action
committees, most of the NGOs

00:41:53.712 --> 00:41:58.917 align:middle line:84%
that are celebrating a cause
are tending to buy the dilemma.,

00:41:58.917 --> 00:42:00.952 align:middle line:90%
the problem that the--

00:42:00.952 --> 00:42:03.388 align:middle line:84%
and there's a place where we
get very over up [phonetic].

00:42:03.388 --> 00:42:06.358 align:middle line:84%
We believe the problem
so strongly

00:42:06.358 --> 00:42:11.162 align:middle line:84%
that that becomes a dominating
thing shaping our consciousness.

00:42:11.162 --> 00:42:15.233 align:middle line:84%
An activism based on that
recreates its premise.

00:42:15.233 --> 00:42:16.735 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Yes, reinforces the
same [multiple speaker].

00:42:16.735 --> 00:42:20.105 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: When we bring that
unhappiness, that anxiety

00:42:20.105 --> 00:42:23.475 align:middle line:84%
that it's a victim
psychology very often.

00:42:23.475 --> 00:42:26.411 align:middle line:84%
You know, the problem with
victim psychology is when I fell

00:42:26.411 --> 00:42:28.747 align:middle line:84%
like I am the victim
of other things.

00:42:28.747 --> 00:42:32.250 align:middle line:84%
I'm focusing on everybody
else's power

00:42:32.250 --> 00:42:35.286 align:middle line:84%
and I don't think I
have any as the victim.

00:42:35.286 --> 00:42:39.824 align:middle line:84%
Well, in so many of these
dynamic, we're buying that.

00:42:39.824 --> 00:42:42.394 align:middle line:84%
As activists, we're buying
into that kind of psychology.

00:42:42.394 --> 00:42:46.498 align:middle line:84%
You have to make that move
from victim to creator.

00:42:46.498 --> 00:42:47.599 align:middle line:90%
We are created.

00:42:47.599 --> 00:42:49.401 align:middle line:84%
Even if there are
many, many factors

00:42:49.401 --> 00:42:51.503 align:middle line:84%
that victimize people
and there are.

00:42:51.503 --> 00:42:54.606 align:middle line:84%
And people deserve
compassion, and care.

00:42:54.606 --> 00:42:57.442 align:middle line:90%
But we all need to find our way

00:42:57.442 --> 00:43:00.445 align:middle line:84%
to our places creators
not just as victims.

00:43:00.445 --> 00:43:05.550 align:middle line:84%
And our way of active--
actively engaging the world

00:43:05.550 --> 00:43:10.155 align:middle line:84%
in sacred bases has to be
basically lit by the joy

00:43:10.155 --> 00:43:15.293 align:middle line:84%
of our communion with the source
of life which is always present.

00:43:15.293 --> 00:43:16.861 align:middle line:90%
I had a big moment.

00:43:16.861 --> 00:43:19.864 align:middle line:84%
I was raised to be an
activist actually, Regina.

00:43:19.864 --> 00:43:25.670 align:middle line:84%
I was raised in a-- in a racial
community back in the 60s.

00:43:25.670 --> 00:43:29.808 align:middle line:84%
I came of age when the Vietnam
War thing was still going on.

00:43:29.808 --> 00:43:31.076 align:middle line:90%
I marched.

00:43:31.076 --> 00:43:33.845 align:middle line:84%
I led. I remember leading
a crowed of 3,000 students

00:43:33.845 --> 00:43:37.082 align:middle line:84%
to march around President
Fleming's home at the University

00:43:37.082 --> 00:43:39.651 align:middle line:84%
of Michigan and Ann Arbor,
and we were wanting them

00:43:39.651 --> 00:43:42.454 align:middle line:84%
to divest their investments
in South Africa.

00:43:42.454 --> 00:43:45.490 align:middle line:84%
And at certain point I saw
this window open up and--

00:43:45.490 --> 00:43:47.659 align:middle line:84%
well, I saw an open
window begin to close.

00:43:47.659 --> 00:43:48.927 align:middle line:90%
So, a woman's arm reached over

00:43:48.927 --> 00:43:50.228 align:middle line:84%
and I could see her
face, and I could see.

00:43:50.228 --> 00:43:52.497 align:middle line:84%
She was just feeling
threatened and anxious,

00:43:52.497 --> 00:43:54.899 align:middle line:84%
and she pulled the drape
as we were marching

00:43:54.899 --> 00:43:58.837 align:middle line:84%
around for home--
probably, his wife.

00:43:58.837 --> 00:44:03.608 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that I didn't
really know how much power he

00:44:03.608 --> 00:44:06.711 align:middle line:84%
had over the investments
of the university.

00:44:06.711 --> 00:44:09.681 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know the
circumstance of her life.

00:44:09.681 --> 00:44:12.917 align:middle line:84%
And I as a pretty
arrogant adolescent though

00:44:12.917 --> 00:44:18.723 align:middle line:84%
that I had a righteous basis for
kind of tormenting this woman.

00:44:18.723 --> 00:44:21.025 align:middle line:84%
But in the-- just a human
confrontation of me marching

00:44:21.025 --> 00:44:22.827 align:middle line:84%
around the home and
seeing her that,

00:44:22.827 --> 00:44:24.996 align:middle line:84%
and I've gotten everybody
to march on his own.

00:44:24.996 --> 00:44:25.764 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:44:25.764 --> 00:44:26.731 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: I actually done it.

00:44:26.731 --> 00:44:27.565 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:44:27.565 --> 00:44:28.566 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: So, I knew-- and I knew

00:44:28.566 --> 00:44:32.303 align:middle line:84%
that I was an arrogant
adolescent punk

00:44:32.303 --> 00:44:34.038 align:middle line:84%
that I hadn't taken
at all into account.

00:44:34.038 --> 00:44:36.775 align:middle line:84%
And that if there was
going to be a revolution

00:44:36.775 --> 00:44:40.145 align:middle line:84%
that was really going to change
things, it had to begin with me.

00:44:40.145 --> 00:44:41.980 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So, how would you
have reframed that with--

00:44:41.980 --> 00:44:45.316 align:middle line:90%
from a mature perspective?

00:44:45.316 --> 00:44:46.384 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: Well--

00:44:46.384 --> 00:44:47.318 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: The same--
let's put yourself back

00:44:47.318 --> 00:44:49.354 align:middle line:84%
in that situation
and reframe it.

00:44:49.354 --> 00:44:53.758 align:middle line:84%
What would you have done from
where you-- what you know now.

00:44:53.758 --> 00:44:54.959 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: You know, it's funny.

00:44:54.959 --> 00:44:57.228 align:middle line:90%
I don't tend to think that way.

00:44:57.228 --> 00:45:00.231 align:middle line:84%
Let's me see if I can play
with that thought experiment.

00:45:00.231 --> 00:45:04.502 align:middle line:84%
I think-- I think that in
the, you know, in reality,

00:45:04.502 --> 00:45:06.671 align:middle line:84%
I think everything was
perfect that the best thing

00:45:06.671 --> 00:45:08.506 align:middle line:84%
that could have happened
is what happened.

00:45:08.506 --> 00:45:10.875 align:middle line:84%
We did what did, she
had the confrontation.

00:45:10.875 --> 00:45:13.144 align:middle line:84%
The president had the
confrontation and the board

00:45:13.144 --> 00:45:16.981 align:middle line:84%
of regents or whoever decided
on their investments realized

00:45:16.981 --> 00:45:19.017 align:middle line:84%
that the poor guy was out
there in the front line--

00:45:19.017 --> 00:45:20.051 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yeah.

00:45:20.051 --> 00:45:20.885 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: -- and they
had to deal with it.

00:45:20.885 --> 00:45:21.920 align:middle line:90%
And I have the insight I had.

00:45:21.920 --> 00:45:23.421 align:middle line:84%
And my life is going
on the very best.

00:45:23.421 --> 00:45:24.122 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:45:24.122 --> 00:45:24.656 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: It's all perfect.

00:45:24.656 --> 00:45:25.723 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:45:25.723 --> 00:45:28.293 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: But certainly
now, I'm interested

00:45:28.293 --> 00:45:31.162 align:middle line:84%
in the different kinds of
activism in which people engage

00:45:31.162 --> 00:45:35.467 align:middle line:84%
with one another in a way that's
profoundly deep spiritually

00:45:35.467 --> 00:45:38.036 align:middle line:84%
and intimately which the inner
work is really being done

00:45:38.036 --> 00:45:41.272 align:middle line:84%
and the outer work is
connected to that in a work.

00:45:41.272 --> 00:45:44.108 align:middle line:84%
In which we really
endeavor to walk our talk.

00:45:44.108 --> 00:45:45.410 align:middle line:90%
We never had the arrogance

00:45:45.410 --> 00:45:47.512 align:middle line:84%
of thinking we're
perfectly walking our talk.

00:45:47.512 --> 00:45:50.215 align:middle line:84%
We always have to walk
it better and better.

00:45:50.215 --> 00:45:51.583 align:middle line:90%
And there's a process

00:45:51.583 --> 00:45:55.420 align:middle line:84%
of becoming more spiritualized
beings who are also engaged

00:45:55.420 --> 00:45:58.489 align:middle line:84%
in the world, who have a
responsibility at the level

00:45:58.489 --> 00:46:00.291 align:middle line:84%
of the transformation
of the world

00:46:00.291 --> 00:46:02.460 align:middle line:84%
that even has a political
dimension.

00:46:02.460 --> 00:46:05.029 align:middle line:84%
But much of our activism
can be in a form

00:46:05.029 --> 00:46:07.532 align:middle line:90%
of creating the technologies,

00:46:07.532 --> 00:46:09.734 align:middle line:84%
or creating new communications
tools,

00:46:09.734 --> 00:46:11.569 align:middle line:84%
or even creating
the kinds of art,

00:46:11.569 --> 00:46:16.107 align:middle line:84%
or changing the way
the spirituality is in,

00:46:16.107 --> 00:46:19.811 align:middle line:84%
there are thousands and
thousands and thousands of ways

00:46:19.811 --> 00:46:22.247 align:middle line:90%
that we can create the elements.

00:46:22.247 --> 00:46:23.948 align:middle line:84%
You might call them
the spare parts out of

00:46:23.948 --> 00:46:28.853 align:middle line:84%
which we can build a new society
in which this species can live

00:46:28.853 --> 00:46:31.990 align:middle line:84%
in a sustainable
relationship to the earth

00:46:31.990 --> 00:46:36.294 align:middle line:84%
in which we can have real
opportunity and justice

00:46:36.294 --> 00:46:37.629 align:middle line:90%
for everybody on the planet,

00:46:37.629 --> 00:46:40.732 align:middle line:84%
in which life can be spiritually
fulfilling for everybody.

00:46:40.732 --> 00:46:44.669 align:middle line:84%
We're building the spare parts
in our projects right now.

00:46:44.669 --> 00:46:46.971 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, you know,
there will be calamities.

00:46:46.971 --> 00:46:48.406 align:middle line:90%
There will be crises.

00:46:48.406 --> 00:46:49.807 align:middle line:90%
And during some of those crises,

00:46:49.807 --> 00:46:51.609 align:middle line:84%
windows of opportunities
will open

00:46:51.609 --> 00:46:55.079 align:middle line:84%
up for more fundamental
systems redesigned.

00:46:55.079 --> 00:46:56.648 align:middle line:84%
And some of us need
to be thinking

00:46:56.648 --> 00:46:59.317 align:middle line:84%
with great foresight
about all of that.

00:46:59.317 --> 00:47:03.087 align:middle line:84%
So, there are so many creative
projects we can be undertaking.

00:47:03.087 --> 00:47:05.990 align:middle line:84%
But the way I look at it,
it's a three-part strategy.

00:47:05.990 --> 00:47:08.493 align:middle line:84%
You know, in the
Ancient Chinese pattern

00:47:08.493 --> 00:47:12.363 align:middle line:84%
that there was a sage
advising the emperor.

00:47:12.363 --> 00:47:14.399 align:middle line:84%
Well, one of the
great Chinese ages

00:47:14.399 --> 00:47:16.501 align:middle line:84%
that we all remember
the name of Bodhidharma,

00:47:16.501 --> 00:47:18.569 align:middle line:90%
the guy with the big eyebrows.

00:47:18.569 --> 00:47:21.873 align:middle line:84%
Well, first we need
to become Bodhidharma.

00:47:21.873 --> 00:47:23.641 align:middle line:90%
We need-- We need to awaken.

00:47:23.641 --> 00:47:26.044 align:middle line:84%
Then we need to do
all the things.

00:47:26.044 --> 00:47:28.379 align:middle line:84%
We need-- We need to come
up with all the solutions,

00:47:28.379 --> 00:47:31.549 align:middle line:84%
all the millions of
forms of activism

00:47:31.549 --> 00:47:32.684 align:middle line:90%
that I was just referring to.

00:47:32.684 --> 00:47:34.686 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: In collaboration.

00:47:34.686 --> 00:47:39.357 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: And-- and-- and-- and
gain the ear of the emperor.

00:47:39.357 --> 00:47:44.128 align:middle line:84%
That is we need to change
our relationship to power.

00:47:44.128 --> 00:47:47.865 align:middle line:84%
It isn't enough to
speak truth to power.

00:47:47.865 --> 00:47:51.269 align:middle line:84%
We have to actually
begin to be willing

00:47:51.269 --> 00:47:54.038 align:middle line:84%
to take responsibility
for this world.

00:47:54.038 --> 00:47:58.376 align:middle line:84%
When you awaken in this world,
you begin to realize that you're

00:47:58.376 --> 00:48:02.513 align:middle line:84%
in a great room with
many, many children.

00:48:02.513 --> 00:48:04.682 align:middle line:84%
As you awaken, it's
like becoming an adult.

00:48:04.682 --> 00:48:08.586 align:middle line:84%
This human species is
going to its adolescence.

00:48:08.586 --> 00:48:12.590 align:middle line:84%
And as you begin to become an
awaked adult, you look around

00:48:12.590 --> 00:48:15.927 align:middle line:84%
and you see that,
these kids they have--

00:48:15.927 --> 00:48:17.462 align:middle line:90%
they don't just have guns,

00:48:17.462 --> 00:48:20.298 align:middle line:84%
they have ridiculously
powerful weapons.

00:48:20.298 --> 00:48:23.134 align:middle line:84%
They're actually raping
and killing one another.

00:48:23.134 --> 00:48:27.372 align:middle line:84%
This is a map, and you look
around as an adult for the eyes

00:48:27.372 --> 00:48:32.010 align:middle line:84%
of other adults, other clear
eyes that see what you see.

00:48:32.010 --> 00:48:37.348 align:middle line:84%
And those eyes meet,
you realize, "Oh,

00:48:37.348 --> 00:48:39.384 align:middle line:84%
we adults have a
responsibility to do

00:48:39.384 --> 00:48:40.652 align:middle line:90%
to bring order to this room."

00:48:40.652 --> 00:48:42.253 align:middle line:84%
We need to take care
of the kids.

00:48:42.253 --> 00:48:44.789 align:middle line:84%
We need to find a way to
separate them from their weapons

00:48:44.789 --> 00:48:45.923 align:middle line:90%
and turn this into a place

00:48:45.923 --> 00:48:48.192 align:middle line:84%
where they can finish
growing up and thrive.

00:48:48.192 --> 00:48:50.194 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And it's interesting
because it--

00:48:50.194 --> 00:48:52.830 align:middle line:84%
well, as you were talking when
you were young during the 60s,

00:48:52.830 --> 00:48:57.902 align:middle line:84%
70s, there was a spirit and
even astrologically plotted

00:48:57.902 --> 00:48:59.137 align:middle line:90%
so to speak.

00:48:59.137 --> 00:49:02.173 align:middle line:84%
A spirit of revolution that
comes around cyclically.

