up and doing variety

00:50:47.812 --> 00:50:49.914 align:middle line:84%
of different practices but
the practice that you do

00:50:49.914 --> 00:50:51.816 align:middle line:84%
in a moment in the
midst of life.

00:50:51.816 --> 00:50:53.718 align:middle line:84%
And I was referring
to that a lot earlier

00:50:53.718 --> 00:50:55.786 align:middle line:90%
in this conversation.

00:50:55.786 --> 00:51:00.024 align:middle line:84%
Basically, many forms of
spiritual practice forget

00:51:00.024 --> 00:51:03.060 align:middle line:84%
to talk about how
it has to happen

00:51:03.060 --> 00:51:05.530 align:middle line:84%
in brief moments many
times all day long.

00:51:05.530 --> 00:51:07.465 align:middle line:84%
Our whole life needs
to be our practice

00:51:07.465 --> 00:51:09.534 align:middle line:90%
and some moment says core.

00:51:09.534 --> 00:51:13.838 align:middle line:84%
Mission has to do with how
the uniqueness of you relates

00:51:13.838 --> 00:51:17.675 align:middle line:84%
to some larger service
that you're here to do

00:51:17.675 --> 00:51:20.244 align:middle line:84%
and really understanding that
so you know the true north

00:51:20.244 --> 00:51:21.979 align:middle line:90%
by which to navigate.

00:51:21.979 --> 00:51:24.081 align:middle line:90%
Milestones are your projects

00:51:24.081 --> 00:51:26.117 align:middle line:84%
like this show is a
milestones practice

00:51:26.117 --> 00:51:28.553 align:middle line:90%
for you creating it each day.

00:51:28.553 --> 00:51:31.455 align:middle line:84%
If you relate to your milestones
practice in three ways,

00:51:31.455 --> 00:51:34.125 align:middle line:84%
it becomes really
self transcending.

00:51:34.125 --> 00:51:36.327 align:middle line:84%
One of them is, I'm
doing it in service

00:51:36.327 --> 00:51:38.529 align:middle line:84%
to something greater
than myself.

00:51:38.529 --> 00:51:41.265 align:middle line:84%
Two is, I'm co-creating
it with a power greater

00:51:41.265 --> 00:51:43.668 align:middle line:90%
than my own creature power.

00:51:43.668 --> 00:51:46.437 align:middle line:84%
And three is, I'm doing
it with willingness

00:51:46.437 --> 00:51:48.005 align:middle line:90%
for it to transform me.

00:51:48.005 --> 00:51:51.142 align:middle line:84%
May the one who completes
this project be different

00:51:51.142 --> 00:51:52.910 align:middle line:90%
than the one who began it.

00:51:52.910 --> 00:51:54.645 align:middle line:90%
That's your milestones practice.

00:51:54.645 --> 00:51:58.216 align:middle line:84%
And then by momentum, I actually
mean all of the other practices

00:51:58.216 --> 00:52:00.918 align:middle line:84%
that are part of life
that I kind of wrote

00:52:00.918 --> 00:52:04.355 align:middle line:84%
about with Ken Wilber in the
book "Integral Life Practice".

00:52:04.355 --> 00:52:07.959 align:middle line:84%
So that includes all the spheres
of our life, our body practices

00:52:07.959 --> 00:52:11.195 align:middle line:84%
with which could be, you know,
running and biking and hiking

00:52:11.195 --> 00:52:14.232 align:middle line:84%
and all of the things that we
do for our physical fitness,

00:52:14.232 --> 00:52:16.701 align:middle line:84%
our diet, all of
those body practices,

00:52:16.701 --> 00:52:20.204 align:middle line:84%
their spiritual practices,
our meditative practices.

00:52:20.204 --> 00:52:25.243 align:middle line:84%
There're mind practices, study,
the audios, and shows like this

00:52:25.243 --> 00:52:28.713 align:middle line:84%
that clarify our
mental understanding.

00:52:28.713 --> 00:52:31.215 align:middle line:84%
There's our psychological
work, our shadow work,

00:52:31.215 --> 00:52:32.583 align:middle line:90%
our development of our souls.

00:52:32.583 --> 00:52:35.753 align:middle line:84%
There's our interpersonal
practice in our intimacies

00:52:35.753 --> 00:52:39.323 align:middle line:84%
and with our family, and also
in our public relationships

00:52:39.323 --> 00:52:41.158 align:middle line:90%
at work and as citizens.

00:52:41.158 --> 00:52:42.727 align:middle line:90%
So, all those are spheres

00:52:42.727 --> 00:52:45.529 align:middle line:84%
and there's an integral cross
training among them that is

00:52:45.529 --> 00:52:47.932 align:middle line:84%
when you're breaking up
stockiness in your body

00:52:47.932 --> 00:52:50.001 align:middle line:84%
and you're breaking up
stockiness on the cushion,

00:52:50.001 --> 00:52:52.370 align:middle line:90%
you grow in both more quickly.

00:52:52.370 --> 00:52:54.171 align:middle line:84%
People who take up
weight lifting,

00:52:54.171 --> 00:52:55.640 align:middle line:90%
actually progress faster

00:52:55.640 --> 00:52:57.541 align:middle line:84%
in their meditation
practice then people

00:52:57.541 --> 00:52:58.876 align:middle line:90%
who don't oddly enough--

00:52:58.876 --> 00:52:59.877 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Interesting.

00:52:59.877 --> 00:53:00.411 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: -- when you
look at the study.

00:53:00.411 --> 00:53:01.779 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yeah.

00:53:01.779 --> 00:53:03.114 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: So, that principle of
integral cross training is a key

00:53:03.114 --> 00:53:04.882 align:middle line:90%
to the way I teach too.

00:53:04.882 --> 00:53:05.650 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Interesting.

00:53:05.650 --> 00:53:06.851 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it's holistic.

00:53:06.851 --> 00:53:10.855 align:middle line:84%
In the big picture-- there
was one thing I wanted

00:53:10.855 --> 00:53:13.791 align:middle line:84%
to get your take on before
we leave the whole subject

00:53:13.791 --> 00:53:14.925 align:middle line:90%
of Heartmath behind.

00:53:14.925 --> 00:53:17.395 align:middle line:84%
It was-- and we talked
about this off camera

00:53:17.395 --> 00:53:20.865 align:middle line:84%
that what had intrigued you most
and you found very validating--

00:53:20.865 --> 00:53:21.699 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: Yeah.

00:53:21.699 --> 00:53:23.701 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes, is that oftentimes--

00:53:23.701 --> 00:53:25.069 align:middle line:84%
please explained
these phenomena.

00:53:25.069 --> 00:53:27.138 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: Yeah, well, there's some
wonderful research that roll

00:53:27.138 --> 00:53:29.940 align:middle line:84%
and some of the other scientist
that Heartmath did having

00:53:29.940 --> 00:53:33.778 align:middle line:84%
to do with-- doing
very, very fine tests

00:53:33.778 --> 00:53:39.950 align:middle line:84%
of when the physiology of
human beings registers events.

00:53:39.950 --> 00:53:44.088 align:middle line:84%
And they discovered
that the first system

00:53:44.088 --> 00:53:46.123 align:middle line:90%
that registers choices

00:53:46.123 --> 00:53:50.494 align:middle line:84%
and senses things is actually
the neurocardiology even before

00:53:50.494 --> 00:53:51.295 align:middle line:90%
the brain that--

00:53:51.295 --> 00:53:52.496 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:53:52.496 --> 00:53:55.032 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: -- our first
perception is hear not here.

00:53:55.032 --> 00:53:58.469 align:middle line:84%
But even more interestingly,
there are many things

00:53:58.469 --> 00:54:03.674 align:middle line:84%
that are anticipated, that is
before the event takes place is

00:54:03.674 --> 00:54:07.345 align:middle line:84%
registered here, that is
we actually are psychic

00:54:07.345 --> 00:54:10.448 align:middle line:84%
that there is-- there is
anticipatory awareness.

00:54:10.448 --> 00:54:12.583 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that is important for us

00:54:12.583 --> 00:54:14.185 align:middle line:90%
to understand is the reason

00:54:14.185 --> 00:54:16.854 align:middle line:84%
that everybody is
feeling like, "Whoa!

00:54:16.854 --> 00:54:18.222 align:middle line:90%
This is game time.

00:54:18.222 --> 00:54:20.858 align:middle line:84%
This is," you know, if I've
becoming more conscious all my

00:54:20.858 --> 00:54:23.027 align:middle line:84%
life, this is the time
to bring it into action

00:54:23.027 --> 00:54:25.863 align:middle line:84%
that the sense that
now is the time.

00:54:25.863 --> 00:54:27.131 align:middle line:90%
Other ages thought they--

00:54:27.131 --> 00:54:29.100 align:middle line:84%
that they were living
in a time that was it.

00:54:29.100 --> 00:54:30.034 align:middle line:90%
No, they were wrong.

00:54:30.034 --> 00:54:31.235 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

00:54:31.235 --> 00:54:33.838 align:middle line:84%
That sense is something
that we're--

00:54:33.838 --> 00:54:37.775 align:middle line:84%
I think we're all getting
in anticipation of something

00:54:37.775 --> 00:54:41.812 align:middle line:84%
that we're being called forth
in the service right now.

00:54:41.812 --> 00:54:46.550 align:middle line:84%
Our hearts, our sensing
mechanisms are sensing something

00:54:46.550 --> 00:54:49.653 align:middle line:84%
that hasn't even happened yet
and we're all kind of it's

00:54:49.653 --> 00:54:52.923 align:middle line:84%
like the triad is gathering to
do the work we're meant to do.

00:54:52.923 --> 00:54:54.025 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Yes, and it
creates a sense

00:54:54.025 --> 00:54:55.659 align:middle line:90%
of anticipation on one hand.

00:54:55.659 --> 00:54:58.596 align:middle line:84%
In some people, it
produces a sense of anxiety

00:54:58.596 --> 00:55:01.232 align:middle line:84%
because we're already
catching the future wave.

00:55:01.232 --> 00:55:04.301 align:middle line:84%
And I was in an experiment
that was conducted

00:55:04.301 --> 00:55:05.236 align:middle line:90%
by Dean Regan [assumed spelling]

00:55:05.236 --> 00:55:07.471 align:middle line:84%
at one point in a
group of people.

00:55:07.471 --> 00:55:09.273 align:middle line:84%
And one of his colleagues
was there.

00:55:09.273 --> 00:55:11.509 align:middle line:84%
I think they may have
been conducting it.

00:55:11.509 --> 00:55:13.611 align:middle line:90%
And it was a very simple one.

00:55:13.611 --> 00:55:17.314 align:middle line:84%
An image is going to pop-up one
side of the screen or the other,

00:55:17.314 --> 00:55:25.122 align:middle line:84%
and you are to click your answer
right or left before it appears.

00:55:25.122 --> 00:55:29.360 align:middle line:84%
And that particular group of
people was amazing the accuracy

00:55:29.360 --> 00:55:33.130 align:middle line:84%
with which some people are
up to 80, 85, even 90 percent

00:55:33.130 --> 00:55:36.801 align:middle line:84%
in their accuracy of where
the image was going to appear.

00:55:36.801 --> 00:55:38.469 align:middle line:84%
And again, this thing
you're talking about,

00:55:38.469 --> 00:55:40.404 align:middle line:84%
it's the heart that's
intercepting

00:55:40.404 --> 00:55:43.741 align:middle line:90%
that pre-information first.

00:55:43.741 --> 00:55:47.812 align:middle line:84%
And so, to understand what you
just said, we are all psychic,

00:55:47.812 --> 00:55:49.814 align:middle line:84%
all of us are beginning
to feel this.

00:55:49.814 --> 00:55:51.916 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't that mean
that we have to engage

00:55:51.916 --> 00:55:56.020 align:middle line:84%
in a very real authentic loving
way with whether it's anxiety

00:55:56.020 --> 00:55:58.956 align:middle line:84%
or anticipation and maybe
ask some deeper questions?

00:55:58.956 --> 00:56:01.759 align:middle line:84%
Maybe like those coons you
were talking about earlier.

00:56:01.759 --> 00:56:03.160 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: Yeah.

00:56:03.160 --> 00:56:10.734 align:middle line:84%
Well, first of all we-- the
first thing that is required

00:56:10.734 --> 00:56:16.040 align:middle line:84%
in order to cope well in
anxiety is to not make it wrong.

00:56:16.040 --> 00:56:19.109 align:middle line:84%
We've got to just allow
that anxiety to be there

00:56:19.109 --> 00:56:24.014 align:middle line:84%
and become curious and self
compassionate in relation to it.

00:56:24.014 --> 00:56:28.919 align:middle line:84%
It will transform but it will
only transform if it's welcomed,

00:56:28.919 --> 00:56:31.755 align:middle line:84%
if we're friendly, if
we in words of rooming.

00:56:31.755 --> 00:56:33.090 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Is therefore--

00:56:33.090 --> 00:56:34.024 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: We've would greet at
the door laughing, you know.

00:56:34.024 --> 00:56:34.725 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:56:34.725 --> 00:56:35.559 align:middle line:90%
It's there for a reason.

00:56:35.559 --> 00:56:36.594 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: It is there for a reason.

00:56:36.594 --> 00:56:37.528 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: It's trying
to get our attention

00:56:37.528 --> 00:56:38.762 align:middle line:84%
for a reason that
knows something.

00:56:38.762 --> 00:56:40.364 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: Exactly.

00:56:40.364 --> 00:56:47.171 align:middle line:84%
So, this is-- that that's key
and then let's though face it

00:56:47.171 --> 00:56:49.073 align:middle line:84%
that anxiety is building
and that sense

00:56:49.073 --> 00:56:51.876 align:middle line:84%
of anticipation is building
because we're facing

00:56:51.876 --> 00:56:52.977 align:middle line:90%
such profound questions.

00:56:52.977 --> 00:56:56.180 align:middle line:84%
How can this globally
interconnected world

00:56:56.180 --> 00:56:58.482 align:middle line:84%
with all the systems that we
have which many of which are

00:56:58.482 --> 00:57:02.786 align:middle line:84%
in crises which seemed
to be in a stuck place.

00:57:02.786 --> 00:57:05.022 align:middle line:84%
We're all kind of
sleepwalking into what seems

00:57:05.022 --> 00:57:07.258 align:middle line:84%
like it maybe a disaster
with global warming,

00:57:07.258 --> 00:57:10.060 align:middle line:84%
and mass extinctions, and
strange weather events,

00:57:10.060 --> 00:57:12.863 align:middle line:84%
and crop failures, and
breakdowns of financial

00:57:12.863 --> 00:57:14.798 align:middle line:84%
and educational, and
so many different kinds

00:57:14.798 --> 00:57:16.367 align:middle line:90%
of institutions, you know.

00:57:16.367 --> 00:57:20.738 align:middle line:84%
That is a question
that we're all facing.

00:57:20.738 --> 00:57:24.108 align:middle line:84%
It's an impossible
question that is growing us

00:57:24.108 --> 00:57:27.044 align:middle line:84%
like Rilca [assumed spelling]
wrote to the young poet,

00:57:27.044 --> 00:57:30.080 align:middle line:84%
"Love the questions, live
the questions let them

00:57:30.080 --> 00:57:31.115 align:middle line:90%
transform you."

00:57:31.115 --> 00:57:33.584 align:middle line:90%
That's what a Rinzai monk does

00:57:33.584 --> 00:57:36.287 align:middle line:84%
when he can't make his
way through his coon.

00:57:36.287 --> 00:57:38.455 align:middle line:84%
He lets the coon
transform his consciousness.

00:57:38.455 --> 00:57:40.691 align:middle line:84%
We have a big question,
all of us,

00:57:40.691 --> 00:57:44.128 align:middle line:84%
millions of us are
facing this big question.

00:57:44.128 --> 00:57:46.931 align:middle line:84%
It's going to take all
of us responding to it

00:57:46.931 --> 00:57:49.333 align:middle line:90%
as practitioners and letting

00:57:49.333 --> 00:57:51.936 align:middle line:84%
that coon change
our consciousness.

00:57:51.936 --> 00:57:56.040 align:middle line:84%
That is how we wake up and
it's how we draw something new

00:57:56.040 --> 00:57:57.441 align:middle line:90%
out of the Noah script,

00:57:57.441 --> 00:58:00.945 align:middle line:84%
how we let the Noetic
evolution take place.

00:58:00.945 --> 00:58:03.948 align:middle line:84%
Cultural and consciousness
evolution will take place

00:58:03.948 --> 00:58:08.252 align:middle line:84%
by us very intensively
becoming the nerve endings

00:58:08.252 --> 00:58:11.989 align:middle line:84%
in the global bring that
draw the lightning strikes

00:58:11.989 --> 00:58:15.159 align:middle line:84%
of that strange attractor of
a higher order that's wanting

00:58:15.159 --> 00:58:16.560 align:middle line:90%
to find its way into form.

00:58:16.560 --> 00:58:17.861 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Allow ourselves to be

00:58:17.861 --> 00:58:20.297 align:middle line:84%
that antenna whether it's
comfortable or uncomfortable

00:58:20.297 --> 00:58:23.534 align:middle line:84%
and then start digging
for its truth.

00:58:23.534 --> 00:58:26.904 align:middle line:84%
>> TP: And it will be both
ecstatic and uncomfortable --

00:58:26.904 --> 00:58:27.571 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:58:27.571 --> 00:58:28.272 align:middle line:90%
>> TP: -- for sure.

00:58:28.272 --> 00:58:30.274 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes, well put.

